<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25595</anchor> <rss>anon.157.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Proof</taxon> <addr>anon.157</addr>  <route>anon.157.xml</route>    </frontmatter> <mainmatter>
 <p>The <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Sections and retractions">section and retraction</link> are built using by postcomposing with the designated <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Sections and retractions">section and retraction</link> of <tex>f</tex>; the witnesses for the postcomposition <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000Y" title="Sections and retractions">sections and retractions</link> are constructed using the <link href="erct-0015.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0015" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions">univalence principle for function spaces</link>.</p>
</mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25596</anchor> <rss>erct-002O.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002O</addr>  <route>erct-002O.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Pushforward along <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> maps</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002O.agda" type="external">erct-002O.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> be <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>; then for any type <tex>C</tex>, the postcomposition map <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( f \circ  - \right ) \mathclose {} \colon   \mathopen {} \left ( C \to  A \right ) \mathclose {} \to   \mathopen {} \left ( C \to  B \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> is <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" addr="erct-000U" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>.</p>
 
   
   
 
</mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25597</anchor> <rss>erct-000Y.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000Y</addr>  <route>erct-000Y.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Sections and retractions</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000Y.agda" type="external">erct-000Y.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>s  \colon  B  \to  A</tex> and <tex>r  \colon  A  \to  B</tex> be a pair of maps. A homotopy <tex>h  \colon  r \circ  s  \sim   1_{ B }</tex> exhibits <tex>s</tex> as a <em><strong>section</strong></em> of <tex>r</tex> and <tex>r</tex> as a <em><strong>retraction</strong></em> of <tex>s</tex>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" numbered="false" root="false"><frontmatter><anchor>25598</anchor> <rss>erct-0015.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Axiom</taxon> <addr>erct-0015</addr>  <route>erct-0015.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local" jonmsterling="addr">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The univalence principle for dependent functions</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0015.agda" type="external">erct-0015.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The reflexive graph structure on <tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } {Bx}</tex> by <link href="erct-0014.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0014" title="Homotopy">homotopy</link> and <link href="erct-0014.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0014" title="Homotopy">identity homotopies</link> is <link href="erct-0010.xml" type="local" addr="erct-0010" title="Path object">univalent</link>.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks/> <references/></backmatter></tree>